<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12039h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12039h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12039h"> 39(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Benignus in druid&apos;s coat / Lucat Mael &mdash; B&apos;s coat / in the / wet &amp; / dry / house</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">St. Patrick offered that the youth Benignus, whom he loved &hellip; should be shut up in a house with the magician: that this house should be made one half of dry faggots and the other of green wood; and that Benignus, wearing the tunic of the magician, should be placed in the house of the dry faggots; and the magician, wearing the tunic of the Saint, be shut up in the house of green wood. <small> Very Rev. Dean Kinane, <a name="TKSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TKSP"><cite title="source">St. Patrick: his life, his heroic virtues, his labours, and the fruits of his labours</cite></a>, (ed. unknown) 105-6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
